The paper deals with coding and communication in a broadcast setting with side information, which is a topic that falls under the information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses general bounds and examples, which involve combinatorial and graph-theoretic concepts, making it relevant to the discrete mathematics (cs.DS) and theoretical computer science (cs.CC) sub-categories. Finally, the paper introduces new coding schemes and phenomena, which could be of interest to the signal processing (cs.SP) sub-category.
